Function Reference/wp original referer field « WordPress Codex
-----------

Retrieve or display original referer hidden field for forms.

The input name is '`_wp_original_http_referer`' and will be either the
same value of
[`wp_referer_field()`](/Function_Reference/wp_referer_field "Function Reference/wp referer field"),
if that was posted already or it will be the current page, if it doesn't
exist.

Usage
-----

` <?php wp_original_referer_field( $echo, $jump_back_to ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$echo` 
:   ([*boolean*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Boolean "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Whether to echo the original http referer.
    Default: true

 `$jump_back_to` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) default is '`current`'. Can be '`previous`' or page you
    want to jump back to.
    Default: 'current'

Return Values
-------------

 (string) 
:   Original referer field.

